.TH ISSY 1 "2026" "issy 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
issy \- a minimal text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B issy
.RI [ options ] " " [ file\fR[:\fIline\fR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B issy
is a tiny, fast, cross-platform text editor written in Zig. It looks like a printed page, not a terminal application. Zero external dependencies.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " file"
Use the specified configuration file.
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " name"
Override theme (default, paper).
.TP
.BI \-\-font " path"
TTF/OTF font file for PDF output.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-config
Skip loading the configuration file.
.TP
.BI \-\-print " output.pdf"
Export the file to PDF and exit without opening the TUI.
.TP
.B \-\-rollback
Swap in the previous binary (from
.IR ~/.cache/issy/issy.prev )
and exit. Only meaningful after the auto-update path has successfully applied an update. Prints an error if no snapshot exists.
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B Ctrl+S
Save file.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Q
Quit (prompts if unsaved changes; press again to discard).
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Same as Ctrl+Q.
.TP
.B Ctrl+F
Incremental search. Type to search, Enter to confirm, Escape to cancel.
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Find next match.
.TP
.B Ctrl+H
Search and replace. Tab switches between fields. Enter replaces current and advances. Ctrl+A replaces all.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Z
Undo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Y
Redo.
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Copy selection.
.TP
.B Ctrl+X
Cut selection.
.TP
.B Ctrl+V
Paste.
.TP
.B Ctrl+A
Select all.
.TP
.B Ctrl+D
Add cursor at next occurrence of word under cursor.
.TP
.B Ctrl+O
Open file (prompts for path).
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
New empty buffer.
.TP
.B Ctrl+P
Export to PDF (requires font_file in config).
.TP
.B Ctrl+R
Reload file from disk (when file has changed externally).
.TP
.B Escape
Clear multi-cursors and selection.
.TP
.B Ctrl+/
Show keybindings overlay (any key to dismiss).
.TP
.B F1
Same as Ctrl+/.
.TP
.B Mouse scroll
Scroll viewport without moving cursor.
.TP
.B Mouse click
Position cursor at click location.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from
.I ~/.issyrc
on POSIX or
.I %APPDATA%\\issy\\config
on Windows. Format is line-oriented:
.PP
.nf
# comment
key = value
key = "value with spaces"
[theme.name]
color_key = "#rrggbb"
.fi
.PP
Keys: tab_width (default 4), expand_tabs (true), line_numbers (true), word_wrap (false), auto_indent (true), auto_close_brackets (false), auto_detect_indent (true), trailing_whitespace (true), indent_mismatch (true), scroll_margin (5), gutter_padding (2), left_padding (1), right_margin (100), cursor_line_bg (true), cursor_style (bar|block|underline), notify_updates (true), autoupdate (false), font_file, font_size (10.0), print_margin_top (72), print_margin_bottom (72), print_margin_left (108), print_margin_right (72).
.SH THEMES
.B default
\- Dark, restrained. Most syntax colors near fg luminance. Keywords violet, strings green, comments nearly invisible.
.PP
.B paper
\- Light, restrained. Same philosophy on white background.
.PP
Design philosophy: restraint. Only 2\-3 token types get real contrast. The eye parses structure through gentle luminance shifts.
.SH PRINTING
Requires
.B font_file
set in config to a TTF/OTF font path. PDF output uses a separate print theme with colors tuned for ink on white paper. Supports syntax highlighting, line numbers, headers, and page breaks.
.SH AUTO-UPDATE
Release builds (those produced by CI, not local dev builds) check for newer versions on startup. A detached background worker fetches the latest release's
.I commit.txt
asset over HTTPS and caches it under
.IR ~/.cache/issy/ .
If the cached commit SHA differs from the running binary's, the status bar shows
.IR "update available: <sha>" .
.PP
With
.B autoupdate = true
in the config, the worker additionally downloads
.IR sha256sums.txt " and " sha256sums.txt.sig ,
verifies the Ed25519 signature against the public key embedded at build time, hashes the downloaded binary against the signed manifest, and stages it as
.IR ~/.cache/issy/issy.staged .
When the buffer is clean and the editor has been idle for 60 seconds, the editor snapshots its running binary to
.IR issy.prev ,
atomically renames the staged binary into place, and re-execs itself with
.BI \-\-resume " path"
so the new instance restores the open file at the same cursor position. The terminal state survives the
.BR execve ,
so the user sees at most one re-render.
.PP
Auto-apply is a no-op for root-owned install paths (the binary is not writable by the running user) and for dev builds. Use
.B \-\-rollback
to revert after an apply, or set
.B notify_updates = false
to disable the whole mechanism.
.PP
On macOS, auto-apply is also a no-op because issy does not ship prebuilt macOS binaries \(em cross-compiled Mach-O from Linux has no code signature and is refused by the Apple Silicon kernel. The notify path still works; run
.B "brew upgrade --fetch-HEAD issy"
to update, or rebuild from source with
.BR "zig build -Doptimize=ReleaseSafe" .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.issyrc
User configuration (POSIX).
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\\issy\\config
User configuration (Windows).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/issy/
Auto-update cache: cached release SHA, signed manifest, staged binary, pre-apply snapshot, and one-shot resume records.
.SH AUTHOR
David Emerson
